Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "preda" in different forms and positions:

1. *Preda*mnom je sto problema koje treba rešiti. (There are a hundred problems in front of me that need to be solved.)
2. Sve se dešava *preda* mojim očima. (Everything is happening in front of my eyes.)
3. Ona me je *preda* svima osramotila. (She embarrassed me in front of everyone.)
4. On se *preda* svim iskušenjima brzo predao. (He quickly gave in to all the temptations.)
5. *Preda* mnom je neizvesna budućnost. (An uncertain future is ahead of me.)
6. Moramo se *preda* zakonom pridržavati određenih pravila. (We must abide by certain rules according to the law.)

In all of these sentences, the word "preda" is used as a preposition meaning "in front of" or "ahead of". The starred form of the word "preda" is used to indicate emphasis.

I hope these examples help!